			<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt; line-height:normal"><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family: "Times New Roman";color:#222222'>All KIPP St. Louis schools are closed through May 29<sup>th</sup>, and are complying with Mayor Lyda Krewson’s</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> mandatory 30 day “Stay at Home” order aimed at preventing further spread of the COVID-19</span><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:#222222'>. We recognize that the closures of schools, businesses and public places puts an extraordinary strain on our KIPP families. KIPP St. Louis is providing resources where possible, including meals at three KIPP school sites, remote learning tools and health and safety information.</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt; line-height:normal"><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family: "Times New Roman";color:#222222'>Our school buildings may be closed, but we’re committed to our students’ educations.</span><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:#500050'> A first </span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">round of remote learning packets was sent home to our students in late March, and our K through 8 students received a second mailing in mid-April. We’re in the process of helping students get connected online and distributing Chromebooks to students who need them, so they can again be together in the “classroom.” <b>Nutritional and learning support services will continue through our last day of school.</b><p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt; line-height:normal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Our goal, and the goal of each KIPP teacher, is to CONNECT with every student. We’re working on getting technology to our students in the hope that all our KIPPsters can be connected through virtual classrooms. Until that happens, each student should expect a call from their teacher at least weekly. Our teachers love and miss their students and, along with calling to check in and answer questions students may have about schoolwork, we want to hear from them about what support they and their families need.<p></p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt; line-height:normal">      </p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt; line-height:normal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">We have created a COVID-19 Emergency Fund to help KIPP provide learning resources to our students, along with other assistance to families Please click on the button below, if you would like to donate.</span></p>
